items.name: Gongjin's Campaign Memorials
items.title: Gongjin's Campaign Memorials
items.headline: Welcome to Gongjin's Campaign Memorials: a Three Kingdoms Encyclopedia
items.desc:
Gongjin's Campaign Memorials is an editable encyclopedia dedicated to collect and consolidate everything known about the historical account of events of the Three Kingdoms period.


Three Kingdoms (''sānguó'' 三國) was an era of disunity. Following the loss of the de facto power of the Han Dynasty the land of China witnessed the rise of rival warlords Cao Cao 曹操, Liu Bei 劉備 and Sun Quan 孫權, each founding their rival states of Wei 魏, Shu-Han 蜀漢 and Wu 吳 effectively splitting the land of China in three.


Three Kingdoms' history has become legend through folklore collected in the 14th century novel ''Romance of the Three Kingdoms'' by Luo Guanzhong and in our modern era serves as a base for many movies (Red Cliff, The Assassins) and videogame series (Dynasty Warriors). The fiction has overshadowed the facts. How different are fact and fiction? Was Liu Bei truly a benevolent hero? Or a warlord who set his sights on power? Was Lü Bu truly the handsome unbested archer riding the era's fastest horse, Red Hare? And how beautiful was Diaochan?


Enter Gongjin's Campaign Memorials and be amazed, surprised or even disappointed when you learn the truth.

items.name: Three's Company Wiki
items.title: Three's Company Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the "Three's Company Wiki"!
items.desc:
Welcome to Three's Company, a wiki devoted to the now classic ABC-TV comedy series which was produced by the production team of Don Nicholl, Michael Ross, and Bernie West, who also produced The Jeffersons, and The Ropers !

The series became a vehicle which would make major stars out of John Ritter and Suzanne Somers, and also would become a star vehicle for co-stars Joyce DeWitt, Richard Kline as well as future cast members Priscilla Barnes and Jenilee Harrison.

You are welcome to browse what we have, create a new article (just click on one of the many red links you see), fix an existing article, or participate in one of our Community Projects to make the wiki a better information source.

items.name: RayWilliamJohnson Wiki
items.title: RayWilliamJohnson Wiki
items.headline: =3 - RayWilliamJohnson
items.desc: Ray William Johnson (born August 14, 1981) is the host of Equals Three and previously Capitol Hill Gangsta. He is in his early thirties and lives in Los Angeles, California. Along with the channel on which he does Equals Three, he has two other channels named BreakingNYC (his former vlog), FattySpins (his former music channel), RunawayPlanet (his vlog) and Yourfavoritemartian (his music channel).

items.name: RayWilliamJohnson Wiki
items.title: RayWilliamJohnson Wiki
items.headline: The RayWilliamJohnson Encyclopedia
items.desc: Equals Three (stylized as "=3") is the name of the show Ray William Johnson hosts and broadcasts from his YouTube Channel. Ray reviews videos he discovers either personally or through a user and usually keeps up-to-date by immediately broadcasting exceptionally viral videos in the following episode. However, more than once has he reviewed older, lesser-known videos he wishes to share. During "pre-production" Ray selects the videos and writes a script revolving around the three which may or may not be relevant to each other.
